HEADWORD: Steading
<hw>Stead"ing</hw> <pr>(st⟦ecr⟧d"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
barns, stables, cattle-yards, etc., of a farm; -- called also
<altname>onstead</altname>, <altname>farmstead</altname>, <altname>farm
offices</altname>, or <altname>farmery</altname>.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
